  How Claude Code uses these files                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                     
  The .codex/skills/ directory                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                     
  These are Claude Code skills — the .codex/skills/ convention is the Codex (OpenAI) agent format, but Claude Code also supports them. Look at the 
  system prompt in this conversation — you can see both skills listed:

  - verus-proof-helper: Help complete Verus proofs for cryptographic functions...
  - verus-spec-helper: Write, review, and tighten Verus specifications...

  Trigger mechanism: When I (Claude Code) detect that the user's task matches a skill description, I invoke it via the Skill tool. The skill's
  SKILL.md gets loaded into context, and I follow its instructions. The references/ files are available for me to Read on demand — they're not
  auto-loaded, but the SKILL.md points to them:

  - references/workflow.md: step-by-step workflow
  - references/techniques.md: proof tactics and patterns
  - references/common-issues.md: common Verus errors
  ...

  So the flow is: user asks to prove something → Claude Code triggers verus-proof-helper skill → SKILL.md loads (~89 lines of instructions) → I read
  specific reference files as needed (techniques.md for tactics, common-issues.md for errors, etc.).

  The docs/ directory

